wikipedia_page.main: Stacey Ross (born 21 October 1973 in London) is an English former professional squash player. He won his first professional tournament in May 2005 and reached a career-high world ranking of 39 in June 2007. He competed multiple times in the British Open. He is currently director of squash at the Wimbledon Club.
